  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Developing an Inhalant Rehabilitation Programme for Street Connected Young People in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Drug addiction is a major problem amongst the thousands of children living on the streets in Uganda, and can prevent them from accessing services or leaving the streets. The main drug used is Mafuta: aeroplane fuel. Mafuta is cheaper to buy than food, and is readily available in urban settings. However, it seriously impairs children&apos;s health, is highly addictive, and can be lethal. This research builds on previous research into the best ways to rehabilitate these children and cure their addiction. It forms the basis for a major new intervention to provide holistic care and support for young people trying to get off Mafuta.</narrative>
  </description>
